Authorities raided the house which had drugs worth a street value of around R100,000. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng police say two people have been arrested for allegedly dealing in drugs after being found in an apparent laboratory in Lanseria. The suspects, aged between 30 and 41, were apprehended after officers received a tip-off about a mushroom drug being sold in Tshwane. Authorities raided the house which had drugs worth a street value of around R100,000. Spokesperson Isaac Mahamba says: "A 41-year-old male and a 30-year-old female were arrested and we confirmed that both of them reside somewhere in Brooklyn. They will shortly appear in court soon and have been charged with possession and dealing of dagga."